  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several important ways:\n\n1. International Conventions and Treaties\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Provide standardized frameworks for combating money laundering\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries collaborate to investigate and prosecute cross-border money laundering\n- Share financial intelligence and evidence\n- Extradition agreements for financial crimes\n\n3. Regulatory Harmonization\n- Standardized reporting requirements\n- Consistent definitions of money laundering\n- Similar due diligence and Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Compliance Mechanisms\n- International banks and financial institutions must follow global standards\n- Sanctions for non-compliance\n- Reporting of suspicious transactions\n\n5. Enforcement Cooperation\n- International law enforcement agencies like Interpol\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Information sharing between national financial intelligence units\n\n6. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Legislation\n- National laws typically incorporate international standards\n- Implement global best practices\n- Align domestic regulations with international frameworks\n\n7. Technological Challenges\n- Emerging technologies like cryptocurrency\n- Need for adaptive international legal approaches\n\nThese intersections create a complex but increasingly coordinated global approach to combating money laundering.",
